From: Varun Gupta <varun.gupta@intel.com>
Subject: [PATCH] drm/pagemap: guard 3-arg zone_device_page_init for older kernels

On v7.0+, zone_device_page_init() takes 3 args (page, pgmap, order).
On v6.6 it takes only the page.

Signed-off-by: Varun Gupta <varun.gupta@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_pagemap.c
@@ -201,5 +201,9 @@ static void drm_pagemap_get_devmem_page(struct page *page,
 				    struct drm_pagemap_zdd *zdd)
 {
 	page->zone_device_data = drm_pagemap_zdd_get(zdd);
+#ifdef BPM_ZONE_DEVICE_PAGE_INIT_3ARGS_NOT_PRESENT
+	zone_device_page_init(page);
+#else
 	zone_device_page_init(page, page_pgmap(page), 0);
+#endif
 }
-- 
